parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of the airbag can cause injuries, distractions, and loss of control while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The airbag deploys suddenly and unexpectedly while driving
without any apparent reason or warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Seat and Airbag Performance in Crash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seats to remain in place and the airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, especially for rear-seat passengers.
symptoms: The front seats collapse backward in a crash
and the airbags fail to deploy despite the severity of the impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt to properly restrain occupants in a crash can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The shoulder strap remains in an upright position despite the occupant being in a prone position
and the stomach portion of the strap remains across the occupant.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure Leading to Unintended Vehicle Movement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, even when the parking brake is engaged, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls or moves on its own
even when the parking brake is set
vehicle strikes an object or another vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure Causing Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: vehicle strikes an object or another vehicle
sudden loss of power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The blistering of the tire sidewall can lead to a sudden loss of air pressure, causing the vehicle to lose control, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Visible blisters or bulges on the tire sidewall
typically on the inside of the tire
which can be detected during routine tire inspections or when replacing tires.
